00:00:10.512 --> 00:00:13.180 position:16% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO] Races that start
with a "Ready, set, go."

00:00:13.313 --> 00:00:14.682 position:33% line:89% align:start
Exam scores.

00:00:14.816 --> 00:00:16.116 position:27% line:89% align:start
Follower counts.

00:00:16.250 --> 00:00:18.385 position:5% line:89% align:start
Restaurants chasing their stars.

00:00:18.520 --> 00:00:21.656 position:21% line:83% align:start
Society is predicated
on hierarchies.

00:00:22.322 --> 00:00:24.391 position:7% line:83% align:start
If every person on this planet
were to be given

00:00:24.526 --> 00:00:26.861 position:5% line:89% align:start
a single all-encompassing rank,

00:00:26.995 --> 00:00:28.830 position:10% line:89% align:start
I wonder where I would place.

00:00:29.664 --> 00:00:31.566 position:19% line:83% align:start
I probably wouldn't be
at the bottom,

00:00:31.699 --> 00:00:34.201 position:10% line:83% align:start
but I definitely wouldn't be
at the top.

00:00:34.334 --> 00:00:35.803 position:16% line:89% align:start
Out of a hundred million,

00:00:35.937 --> 00:00:38.438 position:21% line:83% align:start
I'm betting I'd stand
around ninety-millionth place.

00:00:38.840 --> 00:00:40.140 position:35% line:83% align:start
[ICHINOSE]
Next up.

00:00:40.274 --> 00:00:42.142 position:27% line:83% align:start
Transfer student
turned Academy Representative.

00:00:42.276 --> 00:00:44.846 position:27% line:83% align:start
Hiroto Shinohara
will now address you.

00:00:45.379 --> 00:00:46.581 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
But if I've learned anything?

00:00:46.714 --> 00:00:49.784 position:16% line:83% align:start
It's not to take rankings
at face value.

00:00:49.918 --> 00:00:51.151 position:19% line:89% align:start
What you see before you

00:00:51.285 --> 00:00:53.153 position:33% line:83% align:start
isn't always
what it appears to be.

00:00:53.287 --> 00:00:56.658 position:38% line:83% align:start
You see,
the world is full of lies.

00:00:56.791 --> 00:00:58.292 position:30% line:89% align:start
How's it going?

00:00:58.425 --> 00:01:02.062 position:13% line:83% align:start
My name's Hiroto Shinohara,
your new Seven Star.

00:01:02.630 --> 00:01:05.533 position:19% line:83% align:start
For the next two years,
one person and one person alone

00:01:05.667 --> 00:01:09.369 position:5% line:83% align:start
will reign over you as your lord
and master, and that's me.

00:01:09.504 --> 00:01:11.940 position:19% line:83% align:start
You could be an empress
or an extra.

00:01:12.072 --> 00:01:13.173 position:30% line:89% align:start
Doesn't matter.

00:01:13.307 --> 00:01:15.043 position:38% line:83% align:start
You plebs
aren't getting my Stars.

00:01:15.442 --> 00:01:17.845 position:10% line:83% align:start
If you aren't cool with that,
then come at me any time.

00:01:17.979 --> 00:01:20.347 position:10% line:83% align:start
I'll take your game requests
whenever you'd like.

00:01:20.480 --> 00:01:23.350 position:7% line:83% align:start
That is, as long you don't mind
being absolutely crushed

00:01:23.483 --> 00:01:26.320 position:19% line:83% align:start
and humiliated in front
of the entire student body.

00:01:26.453 --> 00:01:28.255 position:35% line:83% align:start
Try as you
pathetic losers might.

00:01:28.388 --> 00:01:30.123 position:27% line:89% align:start
It's all in vain.

00:01:30.257 --> 00:01:33.193 position:16% line:83% align:start
Because Academy Island's
top rank position...

00:01:33.695 --> 00:01:35.495 position:30% line:89% align:start
Belongs to me.

00:01:36.296 --> 00:01:39.667 position:24% line:83% align:start
Ah, but of course,
that was all a lie.

00:03:14.996 --> 00:03:17.832 position:10% line:83% align:start
How am I supposed to live up
to a speech like that?

00:03:29.110 --> 00:03:31.112 position:35% line:83% align:start
[NARRATOR]
Hello, newcomers.

00:03:31.244 --> 00:03:33.748 position:13% line:89% align:start
Welcome to Academy Island!

00:03:33.881 --> 00:03:36.050 position:33% line:83% align:start
Student life
in this scholastic paradise

00:03:36.184 --> 00:03:39.453 position:7% line:83% align:start
is supported by the very latest
in technological advancement.

00:03:39.587 --> 00:03:41.455 position:24% line:83% align:start
Provided by Japan's
leading company,

00:03:41.589 --> 00:03:42.957 position:16% line:89% align:start
the Saionji Corporation.

00:03:43.256 --> 00:03:45.425 position:10% line:83% align:start
Your rank in this institution
will be determined

00:03:45.560 --> 00:03:48.361 position:7% line:83% align:start
by the number of Stars you have
to your name.

00:03:48.495 --> 00:03:50.765 position:13% line:83% align:start
"But how do I gain stars?"
I hear you ask?

00:03:50.898 --> 00:03:52.767 position:24% line:83% align:start
Well, the quickest
and most convenient method

00:03:52.900 --> 00:03:55.002 position:30% line:83% align:start
is to earn them
by competing in games

00:03:55.136 --> 00:03:56.571 position:13% line:89% align:start
with your fellow students.

00:03:56.704 --> 00:03:58.472 position:13% line:89% align:start
So, play games, win stars,

00:03:58.606 --> 00:04:00.808 position:16% line:83% align:start
and aim for the singular
Seven Star title,

00:04:00.942 --> 00:04:02.977 position:27% line:83% align:start
the highest rank
a student can achieve!

00:04:03.111 --> 00:04:06.147 position:13% line:83% align:start
Your new life as a student,
and your path to a better,

00:04:06.279 --> 00:04:08.415 position:7% line:89% align:start
brighter future, starts today!

00:04:09.650 --> 00:04:10.952 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
I never even wanted

00:04:11.085 --> 00:04:13.087 position:19% line:83% align:start
to become a Seven Star
in the first place!

00:04:13.221 --> 00:04:14.488 position:38% line:89% align:start
So why...

00:04:14.622 --> 00:04:16.891 position:16% line:89% align:start
Is this happening to me?

00:04:18.258 --> 00:04:20.228 position:44% line:89% align:start
Okay.

00:04:20.460 --> 00:04:22.429 position:21% line:89% align:start
If that's me, then...

00:04:22.797 --> 00:04:23.965 position:38% line:89% align:start
I'm lost.

00:04:32.874 --> 00:04:33.975 position:44% line:89% align:start
Um...

00:04:36.409 --> 00:04:37.678 position:38% line:83% align:start
[SARASA]
Yes?

00:04:37.812 --> 00:04:39.147 position:35% line:89% align:start
What is it?

00:04:39.947 --> 00:04:42.850 position:27% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO] Oh, wow.
This girl is like super cute!

00:04:42.984 --> 00:04:45.853 position:19% line:83% align:start
No, wait, scratch that.
She's more pretty than cute.

00:04:45.987 --> 00:04:48.723 position:27% line:83% align:start
Those ruby eyes!
She looks familiar, though.

00:04:48.856 --> 00:04:50.658 position:16% line:83% align:start
Have I seen her somewhere
before?

00:04:50.792 --> 00:04:51.692 position:38% line:89% align:start
An idol?

00:04:51.826 --> 00:04:52.660 position:38% line:89% align:start
A model?

00:04:52.794 --> 00:04:54.061 position:41% line:89% align:start
So, um.

00:04:54.195 --> 00:04:55.563 position:5% line:89% align:start
Did you have a question or not?

00:04:55.696 --> 00:04:57.732 position:16% line:83% align:start
I don't really have a lot
of time to hang around.

00:04:58.199 --> 00:04:59.667 position:35% line:89% align:start
Oh, my bad.

00:04:59.801 --> 00:05:02.570 position:19% line:83% align:start
That is to say, sorry.
I do have a question.

00:05:02.937 --> 00:05:06.174 position:10% line:83% align:start
You see. I only just arrived
on the Island yesterday,

00:05:06.306 --> 00:05:08.375 position:27% line:83% align:start
and well, I think
I might be lost.

00:05:08.910 --> 00:05:11.478 position:19% line:83% align:start
Do you know how to get
to Eimei Academy from here?

00:05:11.612 --> 00:05:14.182 position:33% line:83% align:start
Eimei Academy
is in District Four, right?

00:05:14.314 --> 00:05:15.783 position:19% line:89% align:start
This is District Three.

00:05:17.450 --> 00:05:20.788 position:13% line:83% align:start
Eimei Academy, right here.
Not too good with maps, huh?

00:05:20.922 --> 00:05:23.558 position:35% line:83% align:start
-I'm sorry.
-No need to apologize.

00:05:24.659 --> 00:05:26.861 position:24% line:83% align:start
And you don't need
to be so formal, either.

00:05:26.994 --> 00:05:28.563 position:21% line:83% align:start
You're a second-year,
aren't you?

00:05:28.996 --> 00:05:31.165 position:10% line:83% align:start
That means we're the same age
as each other.

00:05:31.566 --> 00:05:34.769 position:5% line:83% align:start
I guess you're right about that.
Wait, what?

00:05:34.902 --> 00:05:36.436 position:5% line:89% align:start
How'd you know what year I'm in?

00:05:37.004 --> 00:05:38.873 position:24% line:83% align:start
Using your Device,
you can easily access

00:05:39.006 --> 00:05:40.842 position:27% line:83% align:start
basic information
about the people around you,

00:05:40.975 --> 00:05:42.710 position:27% line:83% align:start
like their name,
and academic details.

00:05:42.844 --> 00:05:44.312 position:10% line:89% align:start
Of course, that only applies

00:05:44.444 --> 00:05:46.781 position:7% line:83% align:start
if the person is lower in rank
than you.

00:05:46.914 --> 00:05:49.650 position:19% line:83% align:start
Honestly, I'm surprised
you didn't already know that!

00:05:49.784 --> 00:05:51.085 position:7% line:89% align:start
Aren't device overviews a part

00:05:51.219 --> 00:05:53.554 position:19% line:83% align:start
of the standard student
induction process?

00:05:53.688 --> 00:05:55.289 position:38% line:83% align:start
Ah, well,
I'm kind of in the habit

00:05:55.422 --> 00:05:57.158 position:19% line:89% align:start
of skipping tutorials.

00:05:57.291 --> 00:05:59.492 position:24% line:89% align:start
[giggle] Seriously?

00:05:59.627 --> 00:06:01.329 position:21% line:83% align:start
Are you in the habit
of asking strangers

00:06:01.461 --> 00:06:02.864 position:30% line:83% align:start
to catch you up
on things instead?

00:06:02.997 --> 00:06:06.100 position:21% line:83% align:start
All right, let me see
your Device for a second.

00:06:06.234 --> 00:06:08.903 position:7% line:83% align:start
The Device is an essential tool
for life on the Island.

00:06:09.036 --> 00:06:11.539 position:10% line:83% align:start
Not only is it the one place
you'll find a workable map,

00:06:11.672 --> 00:06:13.274 position:27% line:83% align:start
but its built-in
social media app "Stoc"

00:06:13.406 --> 00:06:15.810 position:13% line:83% align:start
is pretty vital if you want
to keep up-to-date with things.

00:06:15.943 --> 00:06:18.212 position:16% line:83% align:start
You can send and receive
messages through it, too.

00:06:18.346 --> 00:06:21.749 position:7% line:83% align:start
Also, this app is how you send
game requests.

00:06:21.883 --> 00:06:23.084 position:27% line:83% align:start
If you wanna take
someone's Stars,

00:06:23.217 --> 00:06:26.020 position:21% line:83% align:start
then just load it up
and play, 'kay?

00:06:28.055 --> 00:06:29.123 position:30% line:89% align:start
Uh, thank you.

00:06:29.257 --> 00:06:30.490 position:38% line:89% align:start
[giggle]

00:06:30.625 --> 00:06:31.959 position:24% line:83% align:start
[SARASA] That said,
technology is only

00:06:32.093 --> 00:06:33.060 position:21% line:89% align:start
as good as the user.

00:06:33.194 --> 00:06:34.595 position:19% line:83% align:start
The Device isn't gonna
be much help

00:06:34.729 --> 00:06:36.931 position:19% line:83% align:start
if you can't make sense
of the map.

00:06:37.198 --> 00:06:38.666 position:16% line:89% align:start
District four is nearby.

00:06:38.799 --> 00:06:40.501 position:30% line:83% align:start
I can take you
as far as the entrance

00:06:40.635 --> 00:06:43.070 position:16% line:83% align:start
to the major plaza there,
so stay close.

00:06:43.204 --> 00:06:44.437 position:30% line:89% align:start
Oh, sure thing.

00:06:44.572 --> 00:06:48.009 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
Man, she has a cute smile.

00:06:48.142 --> 00:06:50.011 position:38% line:83% align:start
[SARASA]
So if you only got in yesterday,

00:06:50.144 --> 00:06:51.612 position:30% line:83% align:start
does that mean
you're a transfer student?

00:06:51.746 --> 00:06:52.947 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
Yeah.

00:06:53.080 --> 00:06:54.447 position:30% line:83% align:start
Would have been
a pretty lousy first day

00:06:54.582 --> 00:06:56.817 position:35% line:83% align:start
if I missed
the orientation ceremony.

00:06:57.518 --> 00:06:58.786 position:27% line:89% align:start
Oh, that's right!

00:06:58.920 --> 00:07:00.955 position:27% line:83% align:start
Our orientation's
this afternoon, too!

00:07:01.088 --> 00:07:03.624 position:35% line:83% align:start
I gotta go!
This is District Four.

00:07:03.758 --> 00:07:06.560 position:5% line:83% align:start
-Think you can manage from here?
-Ah, yeah. Thank you!

00:07:06.694 --> 00:07:07.862 position:30% line:89% align:start
Right! See ya!

00:07:17.705 --> 00:07:19.874 position:33% line:89% align:start
Are you okay?

00:07:24.845 --> 00:07:27.682 position:19% line:89% align:start
Tell me, and be honest,

00:07:27.815 --> 00:07:30.384 position:7% line:83% align:start
is this what you were planning
the whole time?

00:07:30.518 --> 00:07:32.820 position:19% line:83% align:start
Huh? What do you mean,
planning?

00:07:32.954 --> 00:07:35.256 position:24% line:83% align:start
This was obviously
just a coincidence.

00:07:35.389 --> 00:07:36.791 position:33% line:89% align:start
"Obviously"?

00:07:37.258 --> 00:07:38.592 position:21% line:89% align:start
I wonder about that.

00:07:38.726 --> 00:07:40.928 position:19% line:83% align:start
I mean, you don't look
very surprised to me,

00:07:41.062 --> 00:07:43.764 position:21% line:83% align:start
and this whole thing
has been off from the start.

00:07:43.898 --> 00:07:46.701 position:19% line:83% align:start
A student who can't use
the standard-issue Device?

00:07:46.834 --> 00:07:48.569 position:24% line:83% align:start
Wandering haplessly
around District Three,

00:07:48.703 --> 00:07:50.137 position:13% line:89% align:start
asking directions to Four?

00:07:50.271 --> 00:07:52.740 position:5% line:83% align:start
This plaza was the closest route
between the two.

00:07:52.873 --> 00:07:54.175 position:7% line:89% align:start
You weaponized your ignorance,

00:07:54.308 --> 00:07:56.844 position:10% line:83% align:start
knowing I'd have to lead you
this way myself.

00:07:57.244 --> 00:07:58.546 position:21% line:89% align:start
No, that's not what--

00:07:58.679 --> 00:08:00.748 position:13% line:83% align:start
Quiet! I don't want to hear
your excuses.

00:08:00.881 --> 00:08:03.417 position:19% line:89% align:start
I bet you wanted this.

00:08:03.551 --> 00:08:05.419 position:33% line:83% align:start
Embarrass me,
douse me like a fool

00:08:05.553 --> 00:08:07.221 position:24% line:83% align:start
then take advantage
in the aftermath!

00:08:07.355 --> 00:08:09.857 position:13% line:89% align:start
But it's not gonna happen!

00:08:16.330 --> 00:08:19.033 position:33% line:83% align:start
That does it!
You want a game so bad?

00:08:19.166 --> 00:08:20.067 position:24% line:89% align:start
I'll give you one!

00:08:20.201 --> 00:08:21.702 position:27% line:83% align:start
You're a student
of Academy Island.

00:08:21.836 --> 00:08:23.838 position:5% line:89% align:start
So face me head-on, you coward!

00:08:23.971 --> 00:08:25.673 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
If that's what it takes.

00:08:25.806 --> 00:08:27.675 position:24% line:83% align:start
All I ask I is that
when the game's over,

00:08:27.808 --> 00:08:29.210 position:16% line:89% align:start
you hear me out, alright?

00:08:29.343 --> 00:08:33.147 position:21% line:83% align:start
Oh? Come up with some
clever excuse, did you?

00:08:33.280 --> 00:08:34.749 position:35% line:89% align:start
Fine, then.

00:08:34.882 --> 00:08:36.050 position:10% line:83% align:start
I'll listen to what you have
to say, but that's all.

00:08:36.183 --> 00:08:37.952 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
[sigh] I guess it's a start.

00:08:38.085 --> 00:08:40.221 position:7% line:83% align:start
Hurry up and make the request,
already!

00:08:41.055 --> 00:08:42.623 position:21% line:83% align:start
Are you still playing
the newbie?

00:08:42.757 --> 00:08:44.325 position:16% line:83% align:start
You know as well as I do
that the game request

00:08:44.458 --> 00:08:46.927 position:35% line:83% align:start
has to come
from the lower-ranked player.

00:08:47.328 --> 00:08:50.131 position:16% line:89% align:start
Oh. Sending request now.

00:08:51.532 --> 00:08:53.000 position:13% line:89% align:start
Alright. I've received it.

00:08:53.134 --> 00:08:56.037 position:30% line:83% align:start
So, the details
of the game are...

00:08:56.170 --> 00:08:58.873 position:24% line:83% align:start
Jeez. The requester
has to set parameters

00:08:59.006 --> 00:09:00.941 position:10% line:83% align:start
for the game that the players
can follow.

00:09:01.075 --> 00:09:02.843 position:13% line:83% align:start
If the higher-ranked person
picked the game,

00:09:02.977 --> 00:09:05.012 position:7% line:83% align:start
they could just stack the odds
in their favor and win.

00:09:05.146 --> 00:09:08.015 position:30% line:83% align:start
So, to be fair,
the requester gets to decide.

00:09:08.517 --> 00:09:09.784 position:27% line:89% align:start
But not you, huh?

00:09:09.917 --> 00:09:12.353 position:10% line:83% align:start
I'm just one big joke to you,
aren't I?

00:09:12.486 --> 00:09:14.155 position:30% line:89% align:start
I don't follow.

00:09:14.288 --> 00:09:16.657 position:16% line:83% align:start
The game request you sent
is totally blank!

00:09:16.791 --> 00:09:18.459 position:30% line:83% align:start
You haven't set
any conditions at all!

00:09:18.592 --> 00:09:19.994 position:33% line:89% align:start
Oh, I get it.

00:09:20.127 --> 00:09:21.862 position:24% line:83% align:start
You're so confident
you can beat me at anything

00:09:21.996 --> 00:09:23.764 position:21% line:83% align:start
that you're giving me
free rein to decide?

00:09:23.898 --> 00:09:25.499 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
No, that's not it at all!

00:09:25.633 --> 00:09:26.801 position:16% line:83% align:start
I was just pushing random
buttons!

00:09:26.934 --> 00:09:28.369 position:7% line:89% align:start
I didn't know what they meant!

00:09:28.503 --> 00:09:29.937 position:38% line:83% align:start
[SARASA]
You know?

00:09:30.071 --> 00:09:31.506 position:21% line:83% align:start
It's been a long time
since anyone's made me feel

00:09:31.639 --> 00:09:33.140 position:13% line:89% align:start
an ice-cold fury like this.

00:09:33.274 --> 00:09:35.810 position:5% line:83% align:start
If that's what you want to think
about me, then fine.

00:09:35.943 --> 00:09:38.446 position:13% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO] So? Are you gonna
choose a game, or what?

00:09:38.579 --> 00:09:40.648 position:16% line:89% align:start
You're mocking me! Okay.

00:09:40.781 --> 00:09:43.217 position:27% line:83% align:start
Stay right there
while I get this game set up!

00:09:43.350 --> 00:09:45.920 position:50% line:89% align:start
âª

00:09:54.195 --> 00:09:57.131 position:7% line:83% align:start
A "turn-based staring contest"
on hard mode?

00:09:59.467 --> 00:10:01.869 position:10% line:83% align:start
[SARASA] Ready? Like the name
suggests, this game

00:10:02.002 --> 00:10:04.271 position:24% line:83% align:start
is a harder version
of a staring contest.

00:10:04.405 --> 00:10:07.074 position:10% line:83% align:start
In a normal staring contest,
you laugh, you lose.

00:10:07.208 --> 00:10:10.077 position:27% line:83% align:start
But in this one,
any reaction's a loss.

